## Diagnosis

**The bug is real but incomplete.** The SCSS already has `flex-shrink: 0` on `.logo` and `white-space: nowrap` on `.logoText` — those are correct. The wrapping is caused by a different mechanism: `.logoMark`'s `height` is calculated as `calc($portfolio-type-2xl * 1.2)` and `aspect-ratio: 1`, which means the square mark has a non-trivial minimum size. Under extreme squeeze the **flex row itself** (`navInner`) has no `flex-wrap: nowrap` guard, and crucially the `.logo` block's *two children* (`.logoMark` + `.logoText`) can still wrap relative to each other because `.logo` is `display: inline-flex` but the `gap` can be compressed while `flex-shrink: 0` only prevents the *logo container* from shrinking relative to its siblings — it does not prevent the logo's own children from reflowing.

More critically: **the `tagline` constraint is broken**. The `.tagline` has `min-width: 0` and `overflow: hidden` with line-clamp, which is correct. But `.links` — the flex sibling of `.logo` — does not have `flex-shrink: 1` explicitly, meaning under aggressive squeeze both sides compress together. The logo *container* has `flex-shrink: 0` but if `navInner` itself wraps or the logoMark's aspect-ratio forces a geometry change, the logo name can still end up on two lines.

The real structural gap is: **there is no `white-space: nowrap` on the `.logo` container itself** (only on `.logoText`), and the `.logo` uses `display: inline-flex` rather than `display: flex`. The inline-flex model allows external line-breaking contexts to treat the logo as an inline element and wrap it.

**Anti-pattern citation:** AP-066 (Unconstrained Flex Compression Breaking Identity Text). The fix codifies this as an explicit principle — not just a comment in one SCSS file.

---

## Root Cause

AP-066 — The `.logo` element uses `display: inline-flex`. In certain flex compression scenarios, an `inline-flex` child inside a `display: flex` parent can participate in text-level line-breaking. The `flex-shrink: 0` prevents the *container* from being compressed by the flex algorithm, but it does not prevent the browser from wrapping the `inline-flex` box's *content* if the computed width of the logo container becomes ambiguous. The correct fix is `display: flex` (block-level flex) + `white-space: nowrap` on the container + `flex-shrink: 0` + `min-width: max-content` — a four-property identity lock. Additionally, `flex-wrap: nowrap` must be explicit on `.navInner` to prevent any possibility of the logo dropping to a second row.

The principle has never been formally codified in `docs/design/navigation.md` as a hard rule, nor has AP-066 been fleshed out beyond its title — fixing both is part of this task.

---

## Fix

### 1. `src/components/ui/Navigation/Navigation.module.scss`

Three changes:
1. `.navInner` — add explicit `flex-wrap: nowrap`
2. `.logo` — change `inline-flex` → `flex`, add `min-width: max-content`
3. `.tagline` — verify it is the designated yield surface (no changes needed, already correct)

```scss
@use '../../../styles' as *;

.nav {
  position: sticky;
  top: 0;
  z-index: var(--portfolio-z-sticky);
  background-color: var(--portfolio-surface-terra-subtle);
  box-shadow: 0 4px 12px -4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);

  &::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    height: 10px;
    transform: translateY(100%);
    backdrop-filter: blur(3px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(3px);
    mask-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2), transparent);
    -webkit-mask-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2), transparent);
    pointer-events: none;
  }
}

.navInner {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: nowrap;           // ← ADD: prevents logo from ever dropping to row 2
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  max-width: $elan-container-wide;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: var(--portfolio-spacer-1-5x) var(--portfolio-spacer-2x);

  @media #{$elan-mq-sm} {
    padding: var(--portfolio-spacer-1-5x) var(--portfolio-spacer-4x);
  }
}

.logo {
  display: flex;               // ← CHANGE: was `inline-flex`; block-level flex
                               //   cannot participate in text line-breaking
  align-items: center;
  gap: $portfolio-spacer-0-5x;
  text-decoration: none;
  // Identity lock (AP-066): The nav logo "Yilan Gao" is a hard identity line.
  // It must NEVER wrap, shrink, or collapse under any flex pressure at any
  // viewport width. Four properties enforce this guarantee together:
  //   1. flex-shrink: 0   — logo is not compressed by the flex algorithm
  //   2. min-width: max-content — floor is the logo's own intrinsic width;
  //                               prevents width from collapsing below content
  //   3. white-space: nowrap (on .logoText) — text cannot wrap internally
  //   4. display: flex (not inline-flex) — block-level context; browser cannot
  //                               treat this as an inline box and break it
  // The tagline (.links > .tagline) is the designated yield surface: it absorbs
  // all viewport pressure by wrapping to 2 lines, never more.
  flex-shrink: 0;
  min-width: max-content;      // ← ADD: absolute floor; never narrower than content
  @include transition-fast;

  &:hover {
    .logoMark {
      background-color: var(--portfolio-text-neutral-max);
    }

    .logoText {
      color: var(--portfolio-text-neutral-max);
    }
  }
}

.logoMark {
  display: inline-block;
  height: calc($portfolio-type-2xl * 1.2);
  aspect-ratio: 1;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  background-color: $portfolio-accent-60;
  mask-image: url('/images/yg-logo.svg');
  mask-size: contain;
  mask-repeat: no-repeat;
  @include transition-fast;
}

.logoText {
  font-family: $portfolio-font-serif;
  font-size: $portfolio-type-2xl;
  font-weight: $portfolio-weight-regular;
  line-height: $portfolio-leading-snug;
  color: $portfolio-accent-60;
  letter-spacing: $portfolio-tracking-tight;
  white-space: nowrap;
  @include transition-fast;
}

.links {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--portfolio-spacer-3x);
  // Yield surface: this side of the nav absorbs all viewport pressure.
  // flex-shrink: 1 (default) allows this container to compress.
  // min-width: 0 allows children (notably .tagline) to compress below
  // their intrinsic width and wrap to 2 lines rather than pushing the logo.
  min-width: 0;
}

.link {
  font-family: var(--portfolio-font-sans);
  font-size: var(--portfolio-type-sm);
  font-weight: var(--portfolio-weight-regular);
  color: var(--portfolio-text-secondary);
  text-decoration: none;
  @include transition-fast;

  &:hover {
    color: var(--portfolio-text-primary);
  }
}

.linkActive {
  color: var(--portfolio-text-primary);
  font-weight: var(--portfolio-weight-medium);
}

.tagline {
  @include body-sm;
  color: var(--portfolio-text-secondary);
  // Designated yield surface (see AP-066): the tagline wraps to ≤2 lines
  // under viewport pressure. It NEVER forces the logo to move or wrap.
  min-width: 0;
  text-align: right;
  display: -webkit-box;
  -webkit-box-orient: vertical;
  -webkit-line-clamp: 2;
  line-clamp: 2;
  overflow: hidden;
}
