### 2. `docs/design-anti-patterns.md` — upgrade AP-066

AP-066 currently exists as a title-only stub. Flesh it out with the full pattern, the four-property identity lock, and the yield-surface model. Also add AP-066 to the Navigation & Menus row in the Category Index (it is already listed there — no index change needed).

Find the `<a id="ap-066"></a>` anchor and replace everything through the next `---` with:

```markdown
<a id="ap-066"></a>
## AP-066: Unconstrained Flex Compression Breaking Identity Text

**Status: ACTIVE**

**Trigger:** A nav logo or site name set as `display: inline-flex` with only
`flex-shrink: 0` on the container, causing it to wrap to two lines when the
viewport is squeezed — even though individual text nodes have `white-space:
nowrap`.

**Why it's wrong:** `flex-shrink: 0` only prevents the flex algorithm from
*compressing* the container width. It does not prevent:
- The browser treating an `inline-flex` box as an inline element subject to
  line-breaking.
- The container's computed width from falling below the logo's intrinsic width
  when the flex parent is under pressure and `min-width` is not set.

A site name / logo is a **hard identity line** — it is the irreducible minimum
of brand presence on the page. Allowing it to wrap is never an acceptable
trade-off at any viewport width. The correct approach is a **four-property
identity lock** applied together; any one property alone is insufficient.

**Identity lock (four properties, all required):**

```scss
.logo {
  display: flex;           // block-level flex — cannot participate in inline
                           // line-breaking the way inline-flex can
  flex-shrink: 0;          // excluded from the flex compression budget
  min-width: max-content;  // absolute floor = logo's own intrinsic width
                           // prevents collapse even if flex algorithm is confused
  // on .logoText child:
  // white-space: nowrap;  // text cannot wrap internally
}
```

**Yield surface:** Every nav that contains an identity lock must also designate
a **yield surface** — the element that absorbs viewport pressure instead of the
logo. Typically the tagline or right-side nav links. The yield surface must have
`min-width: 0` (allows flex compression below intrinsic width) and may wrap to
≤2 lines. The nav row itself must have `flex-wrap: nowrap` so the logo can never
drop to a second row.

**Priority rule:** Logo > nav links > tagline.
- Logo: identity lock, never wraps, never shrinks.
- Nav links: may be hidden or collapsed at narrow widths.
- Tagline: wraps to ≤2 lines; the designated yield surface.

**Correct alternative:** See `src/components/ui/Navigation/Navigation.module.scss`
`.logo`, `.navInner`, `.tagline`. See also FB-146.

**Frustration caused:** 1 round. Logo "Yilan Gao" wrapped to two lines under
viewport squeeze. (FB-146)
```

